People in Damaga said dozens of armed men arrived on motorbikes and opened fire. They also stole cattle. In February, nearly 300 girls were taken from a school in Zamfara state. They were later released. Kidnappings and killings are increasing in north-western Nigeria. The authorities in Kaduna state have released a report saying nearly 2000 people in the state were killed or abducted by criminal gangs in 2020.
--BBC--